7. Permissions and APIs that Access Sensitive Information
Disclosure information about NFC Tools and NFC Tools - Pro Edition for Android
To write information on your NFC chips, you may enter sensitive information such as your name, phone number, email, etc.
This information is collected solely for the purpose of writing it to your NFC chip, and it not shared with any third parties and will remain on your device only.
Moreover, our NFC Tools and NFC Tools - Pro Edition apps do not have any internet access rights, they only work offline.
Disclosure information about NFC Tasks for Android
To perform all the tasks stored on your NFC tags, NFC Tasks must have the necessary rights.
As some features of NFC Tasks require special permissions, we wrote these lines to help you understand why we access and use such data.
Every special permission will require your prior consent and you can check the status and detail of each permission in the "Settings" menu, then "Configure permissions" at any moment.
We don't collect and share your personal and sensitive user data, but NFC Tasks can access or use this data to enable features listed below:
APPS: Allows you to list other apps on the device and pick up an app and/or check if your selected app is present on the device.
CALENDAR: Allows you to insert events in your calendar or perform time stamping.
NOTIFICATIONS: Allows you to use tasks that send notifications.
CAMERA: Allows you to open your camera, take pictures or videos.
CONTACTS: Allows you to pick a phone number from your contact list.
LOCATION: Allows you to use tasks and variables related to localization (like {LAT} and {LNG}) or to display a world map.
NEARBY DEVICES: Allows you to use tasks related to nearby devices (such as connecting to Bluetooth devices).
MICROPHONE: Allows you to record an audio file from your microphone.
PHONE: Allows you to make a call and use some variables about your device.
SENSORS: Allows you to get sensors information and use some variables about your device states (like ambient temperature and more).
STORAGE: Allows you to save or load files from your phone's storage.
SYSTEM SETTINGS: Allows you to read or write the system settings on the related tasks.
DEVICE STATISTICS: Allows you to use tasks or conditional blocks related to your running apps.
INTERNET: Some features allow you to send information over the internet (such as tasks to send REST requests or open URLs). You agree that you are solely responsible for data you may send through those features.
