Here is an exhaustive list of data we process in our website and for what purpose?
General browsing on our websites
When you visit our internet website, we collect the data transmitted to our server by your browser.
During your visit, only the data that are technically necessary will be collected. Processing is carried out in the legitimate interest of improving the site's stability and features.
The data will not under any circumstances be transmitted or used for any other purpose.
Customer service / support
As part of a service, we collect data that you voluntarily wish to provide us via online forms or emailing us.
These data are processed exclusively to respond to your requests for information and their processing is based on your consent.
Legal proceedings / requirements
We may use the data we collect to investigate and respond to complaints / dispute or requests from regulatory bodies, government entities or administrative investigations.
4. How do we store and protect your data?
We do not store personal data for longer than is necessary in order to achieve the purposes for which they were collected.
To determine the appropriate storage period, we shall consider the quantity, nature and sensitivity of data and the purposes for which we process.
We delete or anonymise this information in accordance with applicable laws.
We remind you that the collection of your data is used exclusively for the successful delivery of our services and therefore to optimise the experience
To avoid unauthorized access to data and generally secure the data, we apply the following safety measures: encrypted transmission, encrypted storage, an authorization concept, a data backup concept, and physical safety measures for servers. Those safety measures are constantly revised to comply with the latest technological developments.
5. About your rights?
In accordance with the Data Protection Regulations and the legal limits in force, your rights include:
to access your data, particularly to check that they are accurate and exhaustive,
to have your data rectified or erased,
to the portability of the data,
to object to or request a restriction of the processing of your data,
to give specific instructions concerning the processing of your data following your death.
For the processing of your data based on consent, you also have the right to withdraw your consent at any time.
The withdrawal of consent will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
To exercise the rights, please send an email to our DPO.